-- Razgulay, Severstal and Rusal May Be Active: Russian Equity Market Preview
-- B y   S t e p h e n   B i e r m a n
-- 2010-09-22T02:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-22/razgulay-severstal-and-rusal-may-be-active-russian-equity-market-preview.html
The following companies may be
active in Russian trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses and
share prices are from the previous close of trading in Moscow.  The 30-stock Micex Index gained 0.5 percent to 1,433.90 at
the close in Moscow. The dollar-denominated RTS Index rose 0.8
percent to 1,478.21.  OAO Severstal  (CHMF RX): Russia’s largest steelmaker won a
license to develop a coal field in Siberia’s Tyva republic, in a
basin that could become one of Russia’s biggest coal producing
areas. Severstal rose 2.4 percent to 427.77 rubles.  OAO Razgulay  (GRAZ RX): Russian First Deputy Prime Minister
 Viktor Zubkov  said that Russia would boost raw sugar imports
following a drought. The Russian grain and sugar producer rose
0.8 percent to 46.123 rubles.  United Co. Rusal  (486 HK): The world’s biggest aluminum
producer expects prices for the metal to rise as high as $2,500
a metric ton next year. It also expects to boost sales to China
after qualification to sell on the Shanghai exchange. Rusal fell
0.7 percent to $HK8.91 in Hong Kong.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Stephen Bierman  in Moscow 
